00:43:24.300 --> 00:43:25.740
most important one,

00:43:25.800 --> 00:43:26.980
but only because it

00:43:26.980 --> 00:43:28.080
sort of creates a

00:43:28.080 --> 00:43:29.100
coordination between

00:43:29.100 --> 00:43:30.040
pretty much all of the

00:43:30.040 --> 00:43:30.720
other ones is the one

00:43:30.720 --> 00:43:32.060
that Nate started us on

00:43:32.060 --> 00:43:33.300
with on life.

00:43:33.380 --> 00:43:34.080
It's like, what is

00:43:34.080 --> 00:43:35.040
life?

00:43:35.160 --> 00:43:36.800
This sort of act of

00:43:36.800 --> 00:43:37.920
murdering, shedding,

00:43:38.400 --> 00:43:39.260
killing, you know,

00:43:39.420 --> 00:43:40.520
killing, right?

00:43:40.780 --> 00:43:42.260
And then, yeah.

00:43:42.520 --> 00:43:44.140
And, you know, in a

00:43:44.140 --> 00:43:44.760
lot of these, there's

00:43:44.760 --> 00:43:46.300
either different

00:43:46.300 --> 00:43:47.800
variations of that,

00:43:47.840 --> 00:43:48.980
or it's in different

00:43:48.980 --> 00:43:50.820
ways that such, like,

00:43:50.860 --> 00:43:52.540
life does this kind of

00:43:52.540 --> 00:43:53.560
work, which is why I

00:43:53.560 --> 00:43:54.980
turn to, you know,

00:43:55.040 --> 00:43:56.600
how does weakness in

00:43:56.600 --> 00:43:57.680
life do this?

00:43:57.720 --> 00:43:58.880
And how does strength

00:43:58.880 --> 00:44:00.840
in life do this?

00:44:01.640 --> 00:44:03.480
You know, this, how

00:44:03.480 --> 00:44:04.860
does reaction do this?

00:44:04.980 --> 00:44:06.980
How does action do

00:44:06.980 --> 00:44:07.320
this?

00:44:08.000 --> 00:44:09.460
How does taste do

00:44:09.460 --> 00:44:09.780
this?

00:44:09.880 --> 00:44:10.680
How does consciousness

00:44:10.680 --> 00:44:11.420
do this?

00:44:11.580 --> 00:44:12.380
I was talking to

00:44:12.380 --> 00:44:13.960
Kara about this last

00:44:13.960 --> 00:44:14.980
night, where, like,

00:44:15.680 --> 00:44:16.860
thinking about, like,

00:44:16.880 --> 00:44:17.720
sort of a state of

00:44:17.720 --> 00:44:19.200
Nature, or just about

00:44:19.200 --> 00:44:20.120
the brutality of

00:44:20.120 --> 00:44:20.940
nature, right?

00:44:21.020 --> 00:44:21.620
Where there's no

00:44:21.620 --> 00:44:23.020
equality, it's just,

00:44:23.160 --> 00:44:23.840
like, whoever's the

00:44:23.840 --> 00:44:25.140
strongest, you get to

00:44:25.140 --> 00:44:26.020
kill everybody else.

00:44:26.180 --> 00:44:27.220
And it almost seems

00:44:27.220 --> 00:44:28.120
like their entire,

00:44:28.440 --> 00:44:29.220
I mean, I don't

00:44:29.220 --> 00:44:29.760
know, there's probably

00:44:29.760 --> 00:44:31.620
evolutionary data,

00:44:31.640 --> 00:44:32.460
backing this up,

00:44:32.540 --> 00:44:33.480
but there's entire

00:44:33.480 --> 00:44:35.360
species where there

00:44:35.360 --> 00:44:36.660
exists, their purpose

00:44:36.660 --> 00:44:38.200
is just to be eaten

00:44:38.200 --> 00:44:40.040
by the ecosystem,

00:44:40.420 --> 00:44:40.580
right?

00:44:40.620 --> 00:44:41.300
And so there's just,

00:44:41.440 --> 00:44:41.860
like, this

00:44:41.860 --> 00:44:44.240
constitutive unfairness

00:44:44.240 --> 00:44:45.620
or inequality in

00:44:45.620 --> 00:44:46.820
nature, but that you

00:44:46.820 --> 00:44:48.040
can't just simply map

00:44:48.040 --> 00:44:49.700
that onto humanity

00:44:49.700 --> 00:44:50.880
either, because we've

00:44:50.880 --> 00:44:52.340
done something

00:44:52.340 --> 00:44:53.560
different, right?

00:44:53.600 --> 00:44:54.900
But it's also not a

00:44:54.900 --> 00:44:55.940
progression out of

00:44:55.940 --> 00:44:56.800
that either.

00:44:57.480 --> 00:44:58.340
So it's like, I...

00:44:58.340 --> 00:44:58.980
Well, this is what I

00:44:58.980 --> 00:45:00.120
love about what he

00:45:00.120 --> 00:45:01.080
does to that seeming

00:45:01.080 --> 00:45:03.080
being binary, where,

00:45:03.240 --> 00:45:03.740
you know, like,

00:45:04.720 --> 00:45:05.200
this...

00:45:05.200 --> 00:45:05.920
John's brought this

00:45:05.920 --> 00:45:06.440
up, this sort of,

00:45:06.500 --> 00:45:07.420
like, the myth of

00:45:07.420 --> 00:45:08.380
the material basis.

00:45:08.560 --> 00:45:09.340
It's like, you know,

00:45:09.380 --> 00:45:10.200
we're really just

00:45:10.200 --> 00:45:10.980
animals, and we're

00:45:10.980 --> 00:45:11.720
all just really

00:45:11.720 --> 00:45:12.780
unequal, and we're

00:45:12.780 --> 00:45:13.480
all just really

00:45:13.480 --> 00:45:13.960
sort of...

00:45:13.960 --> 00:45:14.380
And then we have

00:45:14.380 --> 00:45:15.440
this facade of,

00:45:15.480 --> 00:45:15.780
you know, the

00:45:15.780 --> 00:45:16.820
social contract

00:45:16.820 --> 00:45:18.720
and this doctrine

00:45:18.720 --> 00:45:19.580
of equality, and

00:45:19.580 --> 00:45:20.500
we pretend like

00:45:20.500 --> 00:45:22.180
things are not...

00:45:22.180 --> 00:45:23.020
are equal when

00:45:23.020 --> 00:45:24.320
they really aren't,

00:45:24.380 --> 00:45:24.920
and, you know,

00:45:25.000 --> 00:45:25.400
like...

00:45:25.400 --> 00:45:25.860
And then that

00:45:25.860 --> 00:45:26.540
becomes...

00:45:26.540 --> 00:45:27.320
That becomes,

00:45:27.320 --> 00:45:28.040
like, really

00:45:28.040 --> 00:45:28.900
shitty justification

00:45:28.900 --> 00:45:30.360
for, you know,

00:45:30.420 --> 00:45:30.880
certain people

00:45:30.880 --> 00:45:31.420
to, like, feel

00:45:31.420 --> 00:45:31.880
like they can

00:45:31.880 --> 00:45:33.300
assert their will

00:45:33.300 --> 00:45:33.880
over someone else,

00:45:33.900 --> 00:45:34.920
or, like, I could

00:45:34.920 --> 00:45:35.540
if I wasn't

00:45:35.540 --> 00:45:36.940
hamstrung by, you

00:45:36.940 --> 00:45:37.700
know, the mores

00:45:37.700 --> 00:45:38.340
of society.

00:45:39.300 --> 00:45:39.700
Right.

00:45:39.920 --> 00:45:41.640
But it seems to

00:45:41.640 --> 00:45:42.240
me that Nietzsche

00:45:42.240 --> 00:45:42.840
just sort of

00:45:42.840 --> 00:45:44.820
destroys, obliterates

00:45:44.820 --> 00:45:46.800
that seeming being

00:45:46.800 --> 00:45:47.720
dichotomy and so

00:45:47.720 --> 00:45:48.040
many things.

00:45:48.060 --> 00:45:48.480
It's like, no,

00:45:49.120 --> 00:45:50.040
this doctrine of

00:45:50.040 --> 00:45:51.500
equality did

00:45:51.500 --> 00:45:52.440
something in the

00:45:52.440 --> 00:45:53.520
world, and not

00:45:53.520 --> 00:45:54.140
just sort of, like,

00:45:54.140 --> 00:45:55.100
at the level of

00:45:55.100 --> 00:45:56.600
social obligation.

00:45:56.820 --> 00:45:57.460
It produced a

00:45:57.460 --> 00:45:58.800
kind of consciousness.

00:45:59.000 --> 00:45:59.700
It produced a

00:45:59.700 --> 00:46:01.720
kind of instinct.

00:46:01.880 --> 00:46:02.440
It produced

00:46:02.440 --> 00:46:03.160
tastes.

00:46:03.420 --> 00:46:03.920
It produced...

00:46:03.920 --> 00:46:05.000
It's, like...

00:46:05.000 --> 00:46:05.240
Right.

00:46:05.300 --> 00:46:05.800
It's a real

00:46:05.800 --> 00:46:06.920
thing in the

00:46:06.920 --> 00:46:09.620
world, not just

00:46:09.620 --> 00:46:10.780
a sort of, you

00:46:10.780 --> 00:46:11.420
know, fake

00:46:11.420 --> 00:46:12.940
accounting of

00:46:12.940 --> 00:46:13.340
the world.

00:46:13.400 --> 00:46:13.860
Yeah, I mean...

00:46:13.860 --> 00:46:14.300
You have to take

00:46:14.300 --> 00:46:14.820
the critique of

00:46:14.820 --> 00:46:15.420
representation

00:46:15.420 --> 00:46:16.260
really seriously.

00:46:16.460 --> 00:46:16.560
Right.

00:46:17.220 --> 00:46:18.120
False representations

00:46:18.120 --> 00:46:19.360
are no less real

00:46:19.360 --> 00:46:20.740
than whatever else.

00:46:20.880 --> 00:46:20.980
Yeah.

00:46:21.060 --> 00:46:21.660
I have to...

00:46:21.660 --> 00:46:22.820
Whenever I teach

00:46:22.820 --> 00:46:23.560
it's certainly

00:46:23.560 --> 00:46:24.500
like genealogy

00:46:24.500 --> 00:46:25.800
in book two,

00:46:25.880 --> 00:46:26.420
where it's, like,

00:46:26.500 --> 00:46:28.060
the figure of...

00:46:28.060 --> 00:46:29.260
The highest figure

00:46:29.260 --> 00:46:29.980
that he envisions

00:46:29.980 --> 00:46:31.200
is the individual,

00:46:31.500 --> 00:46:33.100
like, the supreme

00:46:33.100 --> 00:46:33.940
individual.

00:46:34.400 --> 00:46:35.620
And I always have

00:46:35.620 --> 00:46:36.420
to say, like,

00:46:36.660 --> 00:46:37.660
that doesn't mean

00:46:37.660 --> 00:46:38.800
what every one of

00:46:38.800 --> 00:46:39.320
you thinks that

00:46:39.320 --> 00:46:39.800
it means.

00:46:40.260 --> 00:46:40.980
That it's not

00:46:40.980 --> 00:46:42.040
about I am my own

00:46:42.040 --> 00:46:42.920
dog and I control

00:46:42.920 --> 00:46:43.580
my own destiny.

00:46:43.740 --> 00:46:44.480
Like, and that's

00:46:44.480 --> 00:46:45.420
how everyone reads

00:46:45.420 --> 00:46:46.240
it, and it's very

00:46:46.240 --> 00:46:47.020
easy to read it

00:46:47.020 --> 00:46:47.260
that way.

00:46:47.340 --> 00:46:47.980
Like, there's lots

00:46:47.980 --> 00:46:48.760
of places in Nietzsche

00:46:48.760 --> 00:46:49.780
that sound a lot

00:46:49.780 --> 00:46:50.900
like that kind of

00:46:50.900 --> 00:46:51.320
individual.

00:46:51.520 --> 00:46:52.020
Like, hey, we're

00:46:52.020 --> 00:46:52.680
all individuals,

00:46:52.800 --> 00:46:53.480
and if people

00:46:53.480 --> 00:46:54.100
would stop being

00:46:54.100 --> 00:46:54.900
members of the herd,

00:46:54.960 --> 00:46:55.260
and it's, like,

00:46:55.640 --> 00:46:57.060
this notion of the

00:46:57.060 --> 00:46:58.660
individual, absolutely

00:46:58.660 --> 00:46:59.560
not beholden to

00:46:59.560 --> 00:47:00.700
morality, not beholden

00:47:00.700 --> 00:47:01.080
to sort of

00:47:01.080 --> 00:47:02.200
conceptuality, to

00:47:02.200 --> 00:47:03.760
time, like, it's

00:47:03.760 --> 00:47:05.280
unthinkable, right?

00:47:05.360 --> 00:47:06.080
It is.

00:47:06.700 --> 00:47:07.820
It's so...

00:47:07.820 --> 00:47:09.620
It is not, I am

00:47:09.620 --> 00:47:10.540
my own dog and so I

00:47:10.540 --> 00:47:11.140
should get to make

00:47:11.140 --> 00:47:11.900
my own choices.

00:47:12.140 --> 00:47:13.060
It's, like, no.

00:47:13.320 --> 00:47:14.480
It's not, you're

00:47:14.480 --> 00:47:15.060
making your own...

00:47:15.060 --> 00:47:16.140
That's a consumerist

00:47:16.140 --> 00:47:18.040
version of the

00:47:18.040 --> 00:47:18.360
individual.

00:47:18.720 --> 00:47:19.700
And so, and I...

00:47:19.700 --> 00:47:20.520
And to me, it's

00:47:20.520 --> 00:47:21.460
related to what

00:47:21.460 --> 00:47:22.440
Nathaniel was just

00:47:22.440 --> 00:47:22.900
saying there, it's

00:47:22.900 --> 00:47:23.780
like, there's this...

00:47:23.780 --> 00:47:24.380
I guess you could

00:47:24.380 --> 00:47:25.140
say there's a tension

00:47:25.140 --> 00:47:25.780
or a kind of

00:47:25.780 --> 00:47:26.400
contradiction, but

00:47:26.400 --> 00:47:28.300
there's a desire for

00:47:28.300 --> 00:47:29.840
different forms of

00:47:29.840 --> 00:47:32.260
the same figure

00:47:32.260 --> 00:47:35.040
that emerges in

00:47:35.040 --> 00:47:35.840
some ways

00:47:35.840 --> 00:47:36.720
positively at

00:47:36.720 --> 00:47:38.000
moments, but it's

00:47:38.000 --> 00:47:38.780
always...

00:47:38.780 --> 00:47:39.340
Everything that's

00:47:39.340 --> 00:47:39.820
going to emerge

00:47:39.820 --> 00:47:40.800
positive in place is

00:47:40.800 --> 00:47:41.080
going to be

00:47:41.080 --> 00:47:42.060
problematized somewhere

00:47:42.060 --> 00:47:42.380
else.

00:47:42.440 --> 00:47:43.140
And the same is

00:47:43.140 --> 00:47:43.700
true for everything

00:47:43.700 --> 00:47:44.480
that looks negative

00:47:44.480 --> 00:47:45.340
in places is going

00:47:45.340 --> 00:47:47.040
to be lionized

00:47:47.040 --> 00:47:47.960
someplace else.

00:47:47.960 --> 00:47:48.980
And that's that

00:47:48.980 --> 00:47:50.840
sense of the...

00:47:50.840 --> 00:47:52.680
It both constantly

00:47:52.680 --> 00:47:53.860
gives you a position

00:47:53.860 --> 00:47:56.140
to take and constantly

00:47:56.140 --> 00:47:57.080
undermines the

00:47:57.080 --> 00:47:58.160
position that you

00:47:58.160 --> 00:47:58.820
previously had.

00:47:58.920 --> 00:47:59.540
And that is the

00:47:59.540 --> 00:47:59.960
Hegelian.

00:48:00.080 --> 00:48:01.960
Like, I see, you

00:48:01.960 --> 00:48:02.920
know, that dimension

00:48:02.920 --> 00:48:03.620
of it being the

00:48:03.620 --> 00:48:04.720
Hegelian thing.

00:48:05.100 --> 00:48:06.080
But it also makes

00:48:06.080 --> 00:48:06.320
it...

00:48:06.320 --> 00:48:07.140
I mean, for me, one

00:48:07.140 --> 00:48:07.680
of the things that

00:48:07.680 --> 00:48:08.380
makes Nietzsche much

00:48:08.380 --> 00:48:09.200
easier to read is that

00:48:09.200 --> 00:48:10.540
he's always giving you

00:48:10.540 --> 00:48:11.900
propositions and

00:48:11.900 --> 00:48:12.300
positions.

00:48:12.300 --> 00:48:13.320
like, boom!

00:48:14.080 --> 00:48:14.340
You know?

00:48:14.920 --> 00:48:16.340
And so that's why I

00:48:16.340 --> 00:48:16.940
think that's one of

00:48:16.940 --> 00:48:17.620
the things that's

00:48:17.620 --> 00:48:18.820
really appealing to

00:48:18.820 --> 00:48:20.300
like my 16-year-old

00:48:20.300 --> 00:48:21.180
self when I started

00:48:21.180 --> 00:48:22.160
reading this is it's

00:48:22.160 --> 00:48:23.460
just like punk rock

00:48:23.460 --> 00:48:23.900
mantra.

00:48:24.600 --> 00:48:25.820
Other punk rock

00:48:25.820 --> 00:48:26.300
mantra.

00:48:27.040 --> 00:48:27.420
You know?

00:48:27.600 --> 00:48:28.260
Like, fuck the

00:48:28.260 --> 00:48:29.400
herd, down with the

00:48:29.400 --> 00:48:30.460
norms, and then...

00:48:30.460 --> 00:48:31.580
And again, it's only

00:48:31.580 --> 00:48:34.060
after years of reading

00:48:34.060 --> 00:48:34.980
this stuff that I'm

00:48:34.980 --> 00:48:36.260
like, ah, that

00:48:36.260 --> 00:48:37.380
punk rock mantra

00:48:37.380 --> 00:48:39.080
isn't it.

00:48:39.100 --> 00:48:39.660
There's only one

00:48:39.660 --> 00:48:40.260
tune, yeah.

00:48:40.460 --> 00:48:40.980
That's one...

00:48:40.980 --> 00:48:41.160
Right.

00:48:41.280 --> 00:48:42.020
That's a good way

00:48:42.020 --> 00:48:42.860
because it's there,

00:48:42.980 --> 00:48:43.200
right?

00:48:43.340 --> 00:48:44.560
It is there, but

00:48:44.560 --> 00:48:46.160
it's one tune, and

00:48:46.160 --> 00:48:46.960
there are a lot of

00:48:46.960 --> 00:48:48.360
other harmonics

00:48:48.360 --> 00:48:49.660
laying throughout the

00:48:49.660 --> 00:48:50.220
whole thing.

00:48:50.480 --> 00:48:51.040
Well, it's also...

00:48:51.040 --> 00:48:51.560
I feel like that's

00:48:51.560 --> 00:48:52.720
what lends his work

00:48:52.720 --> 00:48:54.420
to misappropriation.

00:48:54.760 --> 00:48:55.280
You know what I

00:48:55.280 --> 00:48:55.480
mean?

00:48:55.560 --> 00:48:56.860
Like, because if

00:48:56.860 --> 00:48:57.760
you just latch on to

00:48:57.760 --> 00:48:59.320
one aphorism, you

00:48:59.320 --> 00:48:59.900
could be like, all

00:48:59.900 --> 00:49:00.760
right, there's the

00:49:00.760 --> 00:49:02.020
answer, and then...

00:49:02.020 --> 00:49:02.520
Yeah, here's

00:49:02.520 --> 00:49:03.180
Nietzsche's position

00:49:03.180 --> 00:49:03.680
on X.

00:49:03.820 --> 00:49:04.340
And then you

00:49:04.340 --> 00:49:05.420
disregard every

00:49:05.420 --> 00:49:06.240
other aphorism,

00:49:06.480 --> 00:49:07.120
all of which

00:49:07.120 --> 00:49:08.660
complicate the

00:49:08.660 --> 00:49:10.240
proposition and the

00:49:10.240 --> 00:49:11.400
one, you know?

00:49:11.740 --> 00:49:12.460
But in some

00:49:12.460 --> 00:49:13.260
level, what else

00:49:13.260 --> 00:49:13.520
can you...

00:49:13.520 --> 00:49:14.700
You know, I wish I

00:49:14.700 --> 00:49:15.620
had sent this to

00:49:15.620 --> 00:49:15.920
you guys.

00:49:15.920 --> 00:49:16.660
I was just reading

00:49:16.660 --> 00:49:18.280
an interview with

00:49:18.280 --> 00:49:19.460
Daniel Smith, the one

00:49:19.460 --> 00:49:20.640
at Purdue who does

00:49:20.640 --> 00:49:21.520
The Deleuzian stuff,

00:49:21.680 --> 00:49:22.600
and I have to say,

00:49:22.700 --> 00:49:23.260
like, it's really

00:49:23.260 --> 00:49:23.840
great, it's just sort

00:49:23.840 --> 00:49:24.360
of why he's

00:49:24.360 --> 00:49:25.060
interested in Deleuz

00:49:25.060 --> 00:49:26.480
and, you know,

00:49:26.600 --> 00:49:27.300
how it went.

00:49:27.660 --> 00:49:28.300
And he says he's

00:49:28.300 --> 00:49:30.420
like, you know, he

00:49:30.420 --> 00:49:31.220
was at one point

